frameDefinitions: An Entity is obscure, unnotable, and in general little-known.
An Entity is understood to be experienceable within a particular set of delimited Circumstances, which may be more narrowly expressed by a Time, Place.
This frame has to do with nouns denoting types of entities.
An Entity is well-known among a wide range of people (in general or in a particular domain) for a particular Reason, which may be a behavior, characteristic, or some other associated item.
Based on how many Individuals are employed, the Individuals as a whole are described with a Value (either a percentage or absolute number) representing the Employment of the Individuals.
This frame concerns entities conventionally being referred to by particular names.
frameExamples: Geoffrey Rush was <t>little</t> <t>known</t> outside his native Australia when he soared to international prominence.
This type of behavior <t>occurs</t> in several primate mating rituals.
I don't like this newfangled <t><fex name='Subtype'>kind</fex></t> of  fish.
Shakespeare was <t>famous</t> during his life because he performed in front of Queen Elizabeth I more than anyone else.
<t>Unemployment</t> is down, salaries are up for US chemists.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Entity</fen> which is not widely known and rather obscure.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is not well known.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is not famous.
An object or event that is described as being available under delimited Conditions.
A temporal characterization of the circumstances of the existence of an <fen>Entity</fen>.
A spacial characterization of the <fex name=''>Circumstances</fex> of the existence of the <fex name=''>Entity</fex>.
A description of the state of the world in which the <fen>Entity</fen> can be experienced.
The entity which denotes a subtype of the more general <fen>Category</fen>.
The more general type that the target denotes a subtype of. This role is obligatory and should be labeled DNI when not present.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which is widely known and recognized.
The behavior, attribute, or associated entities that provide the reason for the <fen>Entity</fen> being famous.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is famous.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is famous.
The group of people whose employment status is considered.
The property of a group of <fen>Individuals</fen> describing how many of them are employed or unemployed.
The count or percentage of people among the group of <fen>Individuals</fen> that are of the specified employment status.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Value</fen> from the norm.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which <fen>Employment</fen> level of the <fen>Individuals</fen> has a specified <fen>Value</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Individuals</fen> under consideration reside.
<fen>Name</fen> identifies the linguistic expression used to refer to Entities.
The <fen>Entity</fen> is the person the speaker intends to refer to by using a particular name.
listRoleExamples: Certain academic works are obscure <fex>only in North America</fex>.
I don't like this <fex>kind</fex> of fish.
They created a new breed <fex>of dog</fex>.
This station is famous <fex>for the many ramen shacks surrounding it</fex>.
Certain people are well known <fex>only in North America</fex>.
The high unemployment <fex>of the Romany population</fex> is one of the key issues, which need addressing.
The statistics are shocking: <fex><t>unemployment</t></fex> is 57 per cent.
While current unemployment <fex>of about 6%</fex> isn't high by historical standards, there's no denying this trend toward job exportation.
This leads to <fex>high</fex> joblessness in some pockets.
<fex>Last month's</fex> unemployment was 5.17 percent on a seasonally-adjusted basis.

A stadium is expected to cost $350 million, and financial woes caused by recession
and high joblessness <fex>in Oregon</fex> all but rule out public financing.
